                                 <div style="float: left; padding: 5px;"><img src="http://www.jbtours.co.za/images/newsletter/dec%202009/hannes-matthysen.JPG" nosend="1" alt="Hannes Matthysen"><br>
                                   <STRONG><strong><em>Hannes Matthysen</em></strong></STRONG></div>
                                 <p>You have probably noticed that our July 2010 Newsletter (e-zine) looked somewhat different than the previous ones! Thanks for the compliments received from our readers. We trust that it will make reading easier and more enjoyable, as well as ‘softer on the eyes’ as one reader said.</p>
                                 <p>The person behind the changes is Hannes Matthysen, our IT man, and rock band drummer (who returned from a UK tour recently).</p>
                                 <div style="clear:both"></div>
                                 <div style="clear:both;"></div>
                                 <table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                                     <tbody>
                                         <tr>
                                             <td width="87%" bgcolor="#3879af"><font style="padding-left: 5px;" color="#ffffff" face="Georgia" size="4"><strong>THREE EXTRA TRAIN TOURS to CAPE TOWN in DECEMBER 2010</strong></font></td>
                                         </tr>
                                     </tbody>
                                 </table>
                                 <div style="float: left; padding: 5px;"><img src="http://www.jbtours.co.za/images/newsletter/aug-2010/cape-town.JPG" nosend="1" alt="Cape Town"></div>
                                 <p>The popularity of our <strong>Jo’burg to Cape Town</strong> train tours during December has again exceeded all expectations. ALL the tours are fully booked and the enquiries and bookings keep on coming in. In stead of overcrowding the current tours, we have rather <strong>organised three extra train tours</strong> during the peak period – to be hosted at the <strong>same tour price</strong>. The new dates are: 15 – 21 Dec, 22 – 28 Dec & 29 Dec – 4 Jan ’11. <a href="http://www.jbtours.co.za/2010-cape-town-holiday.php">More info</a></p>
                                 <p>These tours are very popular with families and people who can only take leave in December every year. </p>
                                 <table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                                   <tbody>
                                     <tr>
                                       <td width="87%" bgcolor="#3879af"><font style="padding-left: 5px;" color="#ffffff" face="Georgia" size="4"><strong>EKSTRA TREINTOER na KRUGER WILDTUIN (vanaf Kaapstad)</strong></font></td>
                                     </tr>
                                   </tbody>
                                 </table>
                                 <div style="float: left; padding: 5px;"><img src="http://www.jbtours.co.za/images/newsletter/aug-2010/apes.JPG" nosend="1" alt="Apes"></div>
                                 <p>Die artikel in verlede maand se Nuusbrief dat ons ‘n <strong>4de 8-dag treintoer</strong> vir 2010 vanaf <strong>Kaapstad</strong> na die <strong>Kruger Wildtuin</strong> en <strong>Laeveld</strong> gereël het, het weer baie positiewe reaksie en besprekings ontlok. Besprekings vanuit die Wes kaap en Boland is ontvang en selfs vanuit verder plekke soos Oudtshoorn & Albertinia. Hierdie toer, wat vanaf <strong>22 tot 30 Oktober</strong> 2010 aangebied word, waartydens daar o.a. 3 nagte IN die Wildtuin geslaap word, is bykans vol bespreek! (Tans nog 4 plekke beskikbaar). Daar word weer in goeie hotels en lodges oornag en met ‘n luukse lugversorgde bus gery. Toerprys: <strong>R6400 pp</strong> <a href="http://www.jbtours.co.za/2010-kruger-national-park-cape-town.php">Meer inligting </a>                                 
                                 <p>Mense wat in die Noordelike provinsies van die land bly, kan die toer meemaak deur in Johannesburg by die toer aan te sluit teen ‘n verminderde tarief. <strong>R4600 pp</strong> <a href="http://www.jbtours.co.za/2010-kruger-national-park-johannesburg.php">Meer inligting</a></p>
                                 <table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                                   <tbody>
                                     <tr>
                                       <td width="87%" bgcolor="#3879af"><font style="padding-left: 5px;" color="#ffffff" face="Georgia" size="4"><strong>HUISGENOOT SKOUSPEL (by Sun City)  – Vlugte vanuit Kaapstad, George, PE & Durban</strong></font></td>
                                     </tr>
                                   </tbody>
                                 </table>
                                 <p>Die jaarlikse <strong>Huisgenoot Skouspel</strong> wat in Oktober by Sun City in Noordwes aangebied word, beloof weer ‘n groot Skouspel te wees. Dit is die 11de jaar wat dit aangebied word en elke jaar is al 7 die vertonings, met bykans 5000 mense per vertoning, uitverkoop. JB Train Tours reël reeds die afgelope klompie jare bustoere vanuit Johannesburg, Pretoria, asook die Oos en Wes Rand na hierdie feesgeleentheid waar sowat 40 bekende Afrikaanse musikante optree. <a href="http://www.jbtours.co.za/2010-huisgenoot-skouspel.php">Meer inligting</a> Vanjaar is   daar ook &lsquo;n <strong>bustoer</strong> vanaf Nelspruit   gere&euml;l, wat een nag se verblyf insluit. <a href="http://www.jbtours.co.za/2010-huisgenoot-skouspel-nelspruit.php">Meer   inligting</a>. Ons het ook 'n bustoer vanuit Potchefstroom vir Sondag 3 Oktober 2010 gere&euml;l <a href="../2010-huisgenoot-skouspel-potch.php">Meer inligting</a></p>
                                 <p>Sedert 2008 bied ons   ewe gewilde 3-dag naweek <strong>vliegpakkette</strong> vanaf Kaapstad,   George, Port Elizabeth en Durban na die Skouspel toe   aan. <a href="http://www.jbtours.co.za/2010-huisgenoot-skouspel-kaapstad.php">Meer   inligting</a>. Hierdie toerpakket sluit ook verblyf, busvervoer,   sekere etes en natuurlik die Huisgenoot Skouspel kaartjie   in.</p>
                                 <table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                                   <tbody>
                                     <tr>
                                       <td width="87%" bgcolor="#3879af"><font style="padding-left: 5px;" color="#ffffff" face="Georgia" size="4"><strong>WRITE UP in “YOUR FAMILY”</strong></font></td>
                                     </tr>
                                   </tbody>
                                 </table>
                                <p>Go and buy yourself the <strong>August</strong> 2010 edition of the ‘<strong>Your Family</strong>’ magazine at your local store and read the <strong>interesting article</strong> (P. 118), writen by Kate Turner, about <strong>travelling by train</strong> from Jo’burg to Durban. The R21.95 spent on the magazine will be well spent because of a number of other well written articles and beautiful photo’s.</p>
