                                  <ul>
                                    <li>That our banking details <strong><u>HAVE NOT CHANGED</u></strong>. Please be kind enough to advise us should you get a call, fax or e-mail telling you that payment for tours should be paid into another account and not the normal JB Train Tours account. Please be on the look out for this type of fraud.</li>
                                      
                                     <li> That the annual BMW<strong> Motorrad BikeFest</strong> will again be hosted in <strong>Oudtshoorn</strong> over the 2011 <strong>Easter weekend</strong> (22 – 25 April 2011). We are hosting again a train tour to take the bikers from Jo’burg to the event, allowing them more time, with fresh bodies, to enjoy the local routes.</li>
                                      
                                     <li> That the annual and 32nd <strong>Buffalo Rally</strong> will be hosted again by the Nomads of Cape Town from the <strong>18th to 20th March</strong> 2011, again in <strong>Mossel Bay</strong>. We are hosting a train tour from Jo’burg, with motorbikes on the train, for this event as well.</li>
                                      
                                     <li> That you’ll receive the <strong>2011</strong> Year Programme of all our train tours by e-mail this week.</li>
                                     <li>That the Trans Natal Tourist class train has been permamently withdrawn to operate between Jo’burg and Durban – effective 1st August 2010. This has resulted in all our Durban train tours being negatively affected.</li>
